cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the impact of variability on cloud-based big-data workloads, which is a common problem in distributed and parallel computing.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper specifically focuses on the impact of network variability on big-data workloads.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of service provider policies and mechanisms for quality-of-service enforcement on big-data performance.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may touch on security concerns related to big-data workloads in the cloud.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category as the paper does not primarily focus on data structures and algorithms, but rather on the impact of variability on big-data performance.
